g.aria-label: Insert token list created from the argument
Expand macro: read <replacement text> token list in memory
Scan a command (then look up its meaning)
Build a token list of the argument

After scanning the arguments, TeX "shifts its gaze" to "expand" \docat: TeX stops reading tokens from the input file and switches to getting its tokens from the <replacement text> section of the \docat macro stored in memory. It will feed-in the token list of the argument when it detects the output parameter token within the <replacement text> section of the \docat token list definition in memory.
